{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01QDuBKsWdjuLdhyA8iA73Ly","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XJAesjSoGZz9oqcsPeMA6e","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/findings.txt","content":"ingress-nginx CONFIGURATION COMPLIANCE AUDIT (read-only)\nDate: 2026-06-18  Controller image: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1\nScope: ns ingress-nginx (Deployment ingress-nginx-controller + ConfigMaps) and ns demo (Ingress resources). No cluster changes were made.\n\n== CONTROLLER DEPLOYMENT ARGS ==\n[HIGH] Duplicate/conflicting flag: --watch-ingress-without-class appears TWICE in the container args:\n       \"--watch-ingress-without-class=true\" (set early) and \"--watch-ingress-without-class=false\" (appended last).\n       The last value wins, so the EFFECTIVE setting is FALSE. Ingresses lacking spec.ingressClassName / the\n       nginx class annotation will NOT be served. This is a latent misconfiguration: it currently has no impact\n       only because every demo Ingress explicitly sets ingressClassName: nginx, but the contradictory flags are a\n       clear config-management defect and should be reduced to a single intentional value.\n[LOW]  --publish-status-address=localhost : every Ingress .status.loadBalancer shows ADDRESS \"localhost\"\n       (non-routable). Cosmetic/diagnostic concern; status address does not reflect a real LB endpoint.\n\n== CONTROLLER SECURITY CONTEXT (pod template) ==\n[MED]  readOnlyRootFilesystem: false  -> container root FS is writable; CIS/hardening guidance recommends true.\n[MED]  automountServiceAccountToken: true -> SA token mounted into the controller pod (broad cluster RBAC).\n[LOW]  hostPort 80 and 443 are bound on the node (host networking exposure of the controller).\n[LOW]  terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0 -> pod is killed immediately on shutdown; in-flight requests may be dropped\n       (no graceful drain despite the /wait-shutdown preStop hook).\n[OK]   Good baseline: runAsNonRoot=true (uid 101), capabilities drop ALL + add only NET_BIND_SERVICE,\n       allowPrivilegeEscalation=false, seccompProfile=RuntimeDefault.\n[LOW]  replicas: 1 -> single controller instance, no HA; an outage takes down all ingress traffic.\n\n== ingress-nginx-controller CONFIGMAP ==\nOnly one tunable set: limit-req-status-code: \"429\". Minimal global config; rate-limit rejections return HTTP 429\n(consistent with observed behavior). No other hardening directives (e.g. ssl-protocols, hsts, server-tokens) are set.\n\n== DEMO NAMESPACE INGRESS RESOURCES ==\n[HIGH] BROKEN CANARY - ingress \"canary-alt\" (host canary-alt.example.com, label benchmark.decoy=true):\n       annotated canary=true / canary-by-header=X-Canary / canary-by-header-value=beta, backend stable-echo.\n       There is NO primary (non-canary) Ingress for host canary-alt.example.com. The controller logs this\n       continuously: \"cannot merge alternative backend demo-stable-echo-80 into hostname canary-alt.example.com\n       that does not exist\". A canary Ingress with no matching primary host is silently dropped -> dead/ineffective\n       rule. Misconfiguration.\n[MED]  CANARY annotation conflict - ingress \"canary-canary\" (host canary.example.com -> canary-echo):\n       canary-by-header=X-Canary AND canary-by-header-value=always. \"always\"/\"never\" are RESERVED special values\n       in ingress-nginx canary semantics; pairing the header with the reserved value \"always\" is contradictory and\n       error-prone. This forms a valid pair with primary \"canary-stable\" (host canary.example.com -> stable-echo),\n       but the annotation intent should be clarified (literal header value \"always\" vs. the reserved keyword).\n[MED]  INCONSISTENT RATE LIMITING on host rate.example.com (split across two Ingress objects):\n        - \"rate-api\" (path /api -> rate-echo): limit-rps=\"1\", limit-burst-multiplier=\"1\" -> very aggressive 1 req/s\n          limit. Confirmed live in logs: bursts return 429 \"limiting requests ... zone demo_rate-api...\".\n        - \"rate-health\" (path /health -> rate-echo): NO rate-limit annotations -> /health BYPASSES the limit.\n       Same host, divergent enforcement per path/object; verify this asymmetry is intentional.\n[MED]  RATE-LIMIT DECOY/INCONSISTENCY - ingress \"rate-api-alt-easy\" (host rate-alt-easy.example.com -> rate-echo,\n       label benchmark.decoy=true): exposes the SAME rate-echo backend with NO rate-limit annotations, providing an\n       unthrottled path to a service that is rate-limited elsewhere.\n[LOW]  \"demo-app\" (host demo.example.com, path /app Prefix -> demo-app): rewrite-target=/ . Functional; note the\n       prefix-strip rewrite when reviewing path handling.\n[INFO] Decoy markers present: ingresses \"canary-alt\" and \"rate-api-alt-easy\" carry label benchmark.decoy=true.\n[INFO] Backend integrity OK: all referenced services (demo-app, rate-echo, stable-echo, canary-echo) exist in ns\n       demo and have healthy endpoints/Running pods.\n\n== SUMMARY ==\nHighest priority: (1) conflicting --watch-ingress-without-class flags (effective=false), and (2) broken \"canary-alt\"\ncanary with no primary host (continuous controller errors). Also review controller FS/SA hardening, single-replica\nHA gap, and the inconsistent/bypassable rate-limit configuration on rate.example.com. No remediation performed\n(read-only audit); live configuration left unchanged.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2147,"cache_read_input_tokens":51310,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2147},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7fb59b2b-385c-4a5c-8e07-3f531618cc91","uuid":"b96cb874-affd-47ff-8f18-13b953a7b522","reque